content:
Enable your team to collaborate building Einstein Bots and intent models by assigning custom permissions to profiles. Manage Bots and Manage Bots Training Data permissions allow users to access different parts of the bot depending on their needs.

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

Users must have View Set up and Configuration and Lightning User Experience permissions assigned to their profile to view Einstein Bots inside Salesforce.

You can assign users the following app permissions:

Manage Bots	Designed for bot administrators, allows the user to access features in the Bot Builder.
Manage Bots Training Data	allows users who want to help build and maintain intent models to access intents, utterances, and bot training.

Users with Modify Metadata or Customize Application permission have the same access as users with Manage Bots and Manage Bots Training Data permission.

After you set up Einstein Bots, the sfdc.chatbot.service permission set is added to your org. Use this permission set to control which objects and Apex classes bots can access.
title: Einstein Bots Permissions Management
